BronzemanItems		Complete Individual item list
BrzonemanUnlocks	Unlocks that aren't items like prayers, areas, spellbooks
BronzemanItemSets	Anything that unlocks multiple items per unlock
BronzemanPvPTasks	PvP tasks
BronzemanPvMTasks	PvM tasks

Tag rules:
talent		Item or unlock is loaded into the talent tree. This is the only talent-tree switch.
shop		Item appears in the shop. This is mostly a collection signal for now.
melee/range/mage	Combat style for weapons, armor, and style-specific jewellery.
weapon		Equippable weapon. Use with melee/range/mage when style-specific.
armor		Equippable armor or worn gear. Use with melee/range/mage when style-specific.
spec		Weapon has a special attack. Use alongside weapon and its combat style.
jewellery	Amulets, necklaces, rings, and bracelets.
rune		Runes.
food		Food items. Do not also tag these as consumable.
potion		Potions, brews, restores, and antivenom. Do not also tag these as consumable.
teleport	Teleport items and charged teleport jewellery.
ammo		Arrows, bolts, darts, thrown weapons, scales, ether, and spell sacks.
hidden		Item is hidden from the collection page. You can also set hidden, excludeFromCollection, or collectionHidden to true.
consumable	Non-resupply consumable unlock items like MSB imbue scrolls, trouver parchment, imbue scrolls, handles, and attachment parchments.
other		Anything that does not fit another tag.

BronzemanShop tags:
Shop entries use tags instead of category/section.
Use resupply or unlock to decide the shop tab.
Use the normal semantic tags above to decide the shop category heading.

Hardcoded candidates to move into JSON later:
Firebase config and tracker document id live in js/firebase-service.js
Collection filters, category priority, talent tier requirement, and Perilous Moons reward ids live in js/config.js
Challenge definitions/rules live in js/config.js; consider data/BronzemanChallenges.json
Special image folder routing lives in js/assets.js; consider an asset manifest JSON
